				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$CO+{H}_{2}O\to {CO}_{2}+{H}_{2}$$\end{document}

POX (ii) instead uses oxygen to convert methane. The methane partial oxidation reaction is the following:3CH4+12O2→CO+2H2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
