				\begin{document}$${CH}_{4}+\frac{1}{2}{O}_{2}\to CO+{2H}_{2}$$\end{document}

In DMR (iv), CO2 is used as an oxidant to convert CH4 to syngas. The technology is thus very attractive from a sustainability perspective, as it uses two types of greenhouse gases, i.e. CO2 and CH4, to form a valuable product. The process is described by Eq. (3).4CH4+CO2→2CO+2H2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
